<paragraph blockId="44.[831,1436,305,459]" pageId="44" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[831,964,305,328]" pageId="44" pageNumber="119">Comments:</emphasis>
This genus is characterized by 2-segmented labial palpi. Currently, it includes six species, known from 
<collectingCountry box="[902,1021,371,394]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="44" pageNumber="119">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1044,1109,371,394]" name="Nepal" pageId="44" pageNumber="119">Nepal</collectingCountry>
Himalaya, the 
<collectingCountry box="[1307,1432,371,394]" name="Philippines" pageId="44" pageNumber="119">Philippines</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[831,933,404,427]" name="Australia" pageId="44" pageNumber="119">Australia</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[1006,1115,404,427]" name="Mauritius" pageId="44" pageNumber="119">Mauritius</collectingCountry>
. An additional species was found in Lombok.
</paragraph>
